  "color_desc": {
    "kicker": "The color · in plain words",
    "title_html": "What you're <em>looking</em> at.",
    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "Natural Wood sits in the heart of the gray spectrum for Legacy Scotchgard. It reads as a clean charcoal in direct sun and softens to a near-black on cloudy or shaded elevations. That tonal range is the reason it dominates the dimensional asphalt category nationally.",
      "Malarkey uses a tight blend of dark gray and faint blue-gray granules to keep the surface visually alive. The result is a roof that reads as a clean architectural line from the street and a textured surface up close.",
      "A safe specification if you have not committed to a final paint color yet. It cools the rest of the elevation visually and makes warm accents (cedar, stone, copper) look richer."
    ],
